# Session File Format

Sessions are stored as JSONL (JSON Lines) files. Each line is a JSON object with a `type` field. Session entries form a tree structure via `id`/`parentId` fields, enabling in-place branching without creating new files.

## File Location

```
~/.pi/agent/sessions/--<path>--/<timestamp>_<uuid>.jsonl
```

Where `<path>` is the working directory with `/` replaced by `-`.

## Deleting Sessions

Sessions can be removed by deleting their `.jsonl` files under `~/.pi/agent/sessions/`.

Pi also supports deleting sessions interactively from `/resume` (select a session and press `Ctrl+D`, then confirm). When available, pi uses the `trash` CLI to avoid permanent deletion.

## Session Version

Sessions have a version field in the header:

- **Version 1**: Linear entry sequence (legacy, auto-migrated on load)
- **Version 2**: Tree structure with `id`/`parentId` linking
- **Version 3**: Renamed `hookMessage` role to `custom` (extensions unification)

Existing sessions are automatically migrated to the current version (v3) when loaded.

## Source Files

Source on GitHub ([pi-mono](https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono)):
- [`packages/coding-agent/src/core/session-manager.ts`](https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/blob/main/packages/coding-agent/src/core/session-manager.ts) - Session entry types and SessionManager
- [`packages/coding-agent/src/core/messages.ts`](https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/blob/main/packages/coding-agent/src/core/messages.ts) - Extended message types (BashExecutionMessage, CustomMessage, etc.)
- [`packages/ai/src/types.ts`](https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/blob/main/packages/ai/src/types.ts) - Base message types (UserMessage, AssistantMessage, ToolResultMessage)
- [`packages/agent/src/types.ts`](https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/blob/main/packages/agent/src/types.ts) - AgentMessage union type

For TypeScript definitions in your project, inspect `node_modules/@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent/dist/` and `node_modules/@mariozechner/pi-ai/dist/`.

## Message Types

Session entries contain `AgentMessage` objects. Understanding these types is essential for parsing sessions and writing extensions.

### Content Blocks

Messages contain arrays of typed content blocks:

```typescript
interface TextContent {
  type: "text";
  text: string;
}

interface ImageContent {
  type: "image";
  data: string;      // base64 encoded
  mimeType: string;  // e.g., "image/jpeg", "image/png"
}

interface ThinkingContent {
  type: "thinking";
  thinking: string;
}

interface ToolCall {
  type: "toolCall";
  id: string;
  name: string;
  arguments: Record<string, any>;
}
```

### Base Message Types (from pi-ai)

```typescript
interface UserMessage {
  role: "user";
  content: string | (TextContent | ImageContent)[];
  timestamp: number;  // Unix ms
}

interface AssistantMessage {
  role: "assistant";
  content: (TextContent | ThinkingContent | ToolCall)[];
  api: string;
  provider: string;
  model: string;
  usage: Usage;
  stopReason: "stop" | "length" | "toolUse" | "error" | "aborted";
  errorMessage?: string;
  timestamp: number;
}

interface ToolResultMessage {
  role: "toolResult";
  toolCallId: string;
  toolName: string;
  content: (TextContent | ImageContent)[];
  details?: any;      // Tool-specific metadata
  isError: boolean;
  timestamp: number;
}

interface Usage {
  input: number;
  output: number;
  cacheRead: number;
  cacheWrite: number;
  totalTokens: number;
  cost: {
    input: number;
    output: number;
    cacheRead: number;
    cacheWrite: number;
    total: number;
  };
}
```

### Extended Message Types (from pi-coding-agent)

```typescript
interface BashExecutionMessage {
  role: "bashExecution";
  command: string;
  output: string;
  exitCode: number | undefined;
  cancelled: boolean;
  truncated: boolean;
  fullOutputPath?: string;
  excludeFromContext?: boolean;  // true for !! prefix commands
  timestamp: number;
}

interface CustomMessage {
  role: "custom";
  customType: string;            // Extension identifier
  content: string | (TextContent | ImageContent)[];
  display: boolean;              // Show in TUI
  details?: any;                 // Extension-specific metadata
  timestamp: number;
}

interface BranchSummaryMessage {
  role: "branchSummary";
  summary: string;
  fromId: string;                // Entry we branched from
  timestamp: number;
}

interface CompactionSummaryMessage {
  role: "compactionSummary";
  summary: string;
  tokensBefore: number;
  timestamp: number;
}
```

### AgentMessage Union

```typescript
type AgentMessage =
  | UserMessage
  | AssistantMessage
  | ToolResultMessage
  | BashExecutionMessage
  | CustomMessage
  | BranchSummaryMessage
  | CompactionSummaryMessage;
```

## Entry Base

All entries (except `SessionHeader`) extend `SessionEntryBase`:

```typescript
interface SessionEntryBase {
  type: string;
  id: string;           // 8-char hex ID
  parentId: string | null;  // Parent entry ID (null for first entry)
  timestamp: string;    // ISO timestamp
}
```

## Entry Types

### SessionHeader

First line of the file. Metadata only, not part of the tree (no `id`/`parentId`).

```json
{"type":"session","version":3,"id":"uuid","timestamp":"2024-12-03T14:00:00.000Z","cwd":"/path/to/project"}
```

For sessions with a parent (created via `/fork` or `newSession({ parentSession })`):

```json
{"type":"session","version":3,"id":"uuid","timestamp":"2024-12-03T14:00:00.000Z","cwd":"/path/to/project","parentSession":"/path/to/original/session.jsonl"}
```

### SessionMessageEntry

A message in the conversation. The `message` field contains an `AgentMessage`.

```json
{"type":"message","id":"a1b2c3d4","parentId":"prev1234","timestamp":"2024-12-03T14:00:01.000Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Hello"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b2c3d4e5","parentId":"a1b2c3d4","timestamp":"2024-12-03T14:00:02.000Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hi!"}],"provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-5","usage":{...},"stopReason":"stop"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c3d4e5f6","parentId":"b2c3d4e5","timestamp":"2024-12-03T14:00:03.000Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_123","toolName":"bash","content":[{"type":"text","text":"output"}],"isError":false}}
```

### ModelChangeEntry

Emitted when the user switches models mid-session.

```json
{"type":"model_change","id":"d4e5f6g7","parentId":"c3d4e5f6","timestamp":"2024-12-03T14:05:00.000Z","provider":"openai","modelId":"gpt-4o"}
```

### ThinkingLevelChangeEntry

Emitted when the user changes the thinking/reasoning level.

```json
{"type":"thinking_level_change","id":"e5f6g7h8","parentId":"d4e5f6g7","timestamp":"2024-12-03T14:06:00.000Z","thinkingLevel":"high"}
```

### CompactionEntry

Created when context is compacted. Stores a summary of earlier messages.

```json
{"type":"compaction","id":"f6g7h8i9","parentId":"e5f6g7h8","timestamp":"2024-12-03T14:10:00.000Z","summary":"User discussed X, Y, Z...","firstKeptEntryId":"c3d4e5f6","tokensBefore":50000}
```

Optional fields:
- `details`: Implementation-specific data (e.g., `{ readFiles: string[], modifiedFiles: string[] }` for default, or custom data for extensions)
- `fromHook`: `true` if generated by an extension, `false`/`undefined` if pi-generated (legacy field name)

### BranchSummaryEntry

Created when switching branches via `/tree` with an LLM generated summary of the left branch up to the common ancestor. Captures context from the abandoned path.

```json
{"type":"branch_summary","id":"g7h8i9j0","parentId":"a1b2c3d4","timestamp":"2024-12-03T14:15:00.000Z","fromId":"f6g7h8i9","summary":"Branch explored approach A..."}
```

Optional fields:
- `details`: File tracking data (`{ readFiles: string[], modifiedFiles: string[] }`) for default, or custom data for extensions
- `fromHook`: `true` if generated by an extension, `false`/`undefined` if pi-generated (legacy field name)

### CustomEntry

Extension state persistence. Does NOT participate in LLM context.

```json
{"type":"custom","id":"h8i9j0k1","parentId":"g7h8i9j0","timestamp":"2024-12-03T14:20:00.000Z","customType":"my-extension","data":{"count":42}}
```

Use `customType` to identify your extension's entries on reload.

### CustomMessageEntry

Extension-injected messages that DO participate in LLM context.

```json
{"type":"custom_message","id":"i9j0k1l2","parentId":"h8i9j0k1","timestamp":"2024-12-03T14:25:00.000Z","customType":"my-extension","content":"Injected context...","display":true}
```

Fields:
- `content`: String or `(TextContent | ImageContent)[]` (same as UserMessage)
- `display`: `true` = show in TUI with distinct styling, `false` = hidden
- `details`: Optional extension-specific metadata (not sent to LLM)

### LabelEntry

User-defined bookmark/marker on an entry.

```json
{"type":"label","id":"j0k1l2m3","parentId":"i9j0k1l2","timestamp":"2024-12-03T14:30:00.000Z","targetId":"a1b2c3d4","label":"checkpoint-1"}
```

Set `label` to `undefined` to clear a label.

### SessionInfoEntry

Session metadata (e.g., user-defined display name). Set via `/name` command or `pi.setSessionName()` in extensions.

```json
{"type":"session_info","id":"k1l2m3n4","parentId":"j0k1l2m3","timestamp":"2024-12-03T14:35:00.000Z","name":"Refactor auth module"}
```

The session name is displayed in the session selector (`/resume`) instead of the first message when set.

## Tree Structure

Entries form a tree:
- First entry has `parentId: null`
- Each subsequent entry points to its parent via `parentId`
- Branching creates new children from an earlier entry
- The "leaf" is the current position in the tree

```
[user msg] ─── [assistant] ─── [user msg] ─── [assistant] ─┬─ [user msg] ← current leaf
                                                            │
                                                            └─ [branch_summary] ─── [user msg] ← alternate branch
```

## Context Building

`buildSessionContext()` walks from the current leaf to the root, producing the message list for the LLM:

1. Collects all entries on the path
2. Extracts current model and thinking level settings
3. If a `CompactionEntry` is on the path:
   - Emits the summary first
   - Then messages from `firstKeptEntryId` to compaction
   - Then messages after compaction
4. Converts `BranchSummaryEntry` and `CustomMessageEntry` to appropriate message formats

## Parsing Example

```typescript
import { readFileSync } from "fs";

const lines = readFileSync("session.jsonl", "utf8").trim().split("\n");

for (const line of lines) {
  const entry = JSON.parse(line);

  switch (entry.type) {
    case "session":
      console.log(`Session v${entry.version ?? 1}: ${entry.id}`);
      break;
    case "message":
      console.log(`[${entry.id}] ${entry.message.role}: ${JSON.stringify(entry.message.content)}`);
      break;
    case "compaction":
      console.log(`[${entry.id}] Compaction: ${entry.tokensBefore} tokens summarized`);
      break;
    case "branch_summary":
      console.log(`[${entry.id}] Branch from ${entry.fromId}`);
      break;
    case "custom":
      console.log(`[${entry.id}] Custom (${entry.customType}): ${JSON.stringify(entry.data)}`);
      break;
    case "custom_message":
      console.log(`[${entry.id}] Extension message (${entry.customType}): ${entry.content}`);
      break;
    case "label":
      console.log(`[${entry.id}] Label "${entry.label}" on ${entry.targetId}`);
      break;
    case "model_change":
      console.log(`[${entry.id}] Model: ${entry.provider}/${entry.modelId}`);
      break;
    case "thinking_level_change":
      console.log(`[${entry.id}] Thinking: ${entry.thinkingLevel}`);
      break;
  }
}
```

## SessionManager API

Key methods for working with sessions programmatically.

### Static Creation Methods
- `SessionManager.create(cwd, sessionDir?)` - New session
- `SessionManager.open(path, sessionDir?)` - Open existing session file
- `SessionManager.continueRecent(cwd, sessionDir?)` - Continue most recent or create new
- `SessionManager.inMemory(cwd?)` - No file persistence
- `SessionManager.forkFrom(sourcePath, targetCwd, sessionDir?)` - Fork session from another project

### Static Listing Methods
- `SessionManager.list(cwd, sessionDir?, onProgress?)` - List sessions for a directory
- `SessionManager.listAll(onProgress?)` - List all sessions across all projects

### Instance Methods - Session Management
- `newSession(options?)` - Start a new session (options: `{ parentSession?: string }`)
- `setSessionFile(path)` - Switch to a different session file
- `createBranchedSession(leafId)` - Extract branch to new session file

### Instance Methods - Appending (all return entry ID)
- `appendMessage(message)` - Add message
- `appendThinkingLevelChange(level)` - Record thinking change
- `appendModelChange(provider, modelId)` - Record model change
- `appendCompaction(summary, firstKeptEntryId, tokensBefore, details?, fromHook?)` - Add compaction
- `appendCustomEntry(customType, data?)` - Extension state (not in context)
- `appendSessionInfo(name)` - Set session display name
- `appendCustomMessageEntry(customType, content, display, details?)` - Extension message (in context)
- `appendLabelChange(targetId, label)` - Set/clear label

### Instance Methods - Tree Navigation
- `getLeafId()` - Current position
- `getLeafEntry()` - Get current leaf entry
- `getEntry(id)` - Get entry by ID
- `getBranch(fromId?)` - Walk from entry to root
- `getTree()` - Get full tree structure
- `getChildren(parentId)` - Get direct children
- `getLabel(id)` - Get label for entry
- `branch(entryId)` - Move leaf to earlier entry
- `resetLeaf()` - Reset leaf to null (before any entries)
- `branchWithSummary(entryId, summary, details?, fromHook?)` - Branch with context summary

### Instance Methods - Context & Info
- `buildSessionContext()` - Get messages, thinkingLevel, and model for LLM
- `getEntries()` - All entries (excluding header)
- `getHeader()` - Session header metadata
- `getSessionName()` - Get display name from latest session_info entry
- `getCwd()` - Working directory
- `getSessionDir()` - Session storage directory
- `getSessionId()` - Session UUID
- `getSessionFile()` - Session file path (undefined for in-memory)
- `isPersisted()` - Whether session is saved to disk

Based on my search of the pi documentation and examples, **there is no "session-switch" extension**. Session switching is a **built-in feature** of pi. Here's how to use it:

## Built-in Session Switching

### 1. **Interactive Commands**

**Switch to an existing session:**
```bash
/resume
```
This opens a selector showing all your saved sessions. You can:
- Navigate with arrow keys and press Enter to switch
- Press `Ctrl+D` to delete a session

**Start a new session:**
```bash
/new
```

**Fork current session:**
```bash
/fork
```
Creates a new session file branched from the current point.

### 2. **Programmatic Session Switching (in Extensions)**

If you want to build custom session switching logic, you can create an extension:

```typescript
import type { ExtensionAPI } from "@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent";
import { SessionManager } from "@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent";

export default function (pi: ExtensionAPI) {
  // Register a custom session switcher command
  pi.registerCommand("switch", {
    description: "Switch to another session",
    handler: async (args, ctx) => {
      // List available sessions
      const sessions = await SessionManager.list(ctx.cwd);

      if (sessions.length === 0) {
        ctx.ui.notify("No sessions found", "info");
        return;
      }

      // Let user pick a session
      const choice = await ctx.ui.select(
        "Pick session:",
        sessions.map(s => s.file)
      );

      if (choice) {
        await ctx.switchSession(choice);
      }
    },
  });
}
```

### 3. **Session Events**

Extensions can also intercept session switching:

```typescript
pi.on("session_before_switch", async (event, ctx) => {
  // event.reason - "new" or "resume"
  // event.targetSessionFile - session we're switching to (only for "resume")

  // Cancel the switch if needed
  if (someCondition) {
    return { cancel: true };
  }
});
```

## Summary

- **No separate extension needed** - use `/resume` and `/new` commands
- **For custom behavior** - create your own extension using `ctx.switchSession()` and `SessionManager.list()`
- **See `confirm-destructive.ts` example** in the pi extensions folder for intercepting session switches

Is there a specific session switching workflow you're trying to accomplish? I can help you create a custom extension for that!

package com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.operations.commissions

import com.glossgenius.core.applications.context.RequestContext
import com.glossgenius.core.applications.logs.Logger
import com.glossgenius.core.jobs.toJobContext
import com.glossgenius.core.libs.tokens.domains.spaces.LocationToken
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.configuration.jobs.commissions.DualCommissionReportJob
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.configuration.jobs.commissions.DualCommissionReportJobParams
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.models.commissions.CommissionPolicy
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.models.commissions.report.CommissionReport
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.operations.payroll.helpers.IndexCommissionPoliciesHelper
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.stores.CoreApiStore
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.stores.CoreFeaturesStore
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.stores.LocationStore
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.stores.business.BusinessMembersStore
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.stores.commissions.CommissionPolicyStore
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.stores.commissions.CommissionReportLineItemStore
import jakarta.inject.Singleton
import org.jobrunr.scheduling.JobRequestScheduler
import java.time.LocalDate
import java.time.OffsetDateTime
import java.time.ZoneId
import java.time.ZoneOffset
import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.models.commissions.CreateCommissionReportParameters as CommissionReportParameters

/**
 * Operation to create commission reports.
 */
@Singleton
class CreateCommissionReportOperation(
    private val coreApiStore: CoreApiStore,
    private val commissionPolicyStore: CommissionPolicyStore,
    private val commissionReportLineItemStore: CommissionReportLineItemStore,
    private val indexCommissionPoliciesHelper: IndexCommissionPoliciesHelper,
    private val coreFeaturesStore: CoreFeaturesStore,
    private val businessMemberStore: BusinessMembersStore,
    private val locationStore: LocationStore,
    private val requestContext: RequestContext,
    private val logger: Logger,
    private val jobRequestScheduler: JobRequestScheduler,
) {
    /**
     * Main entry point to create a commission report.
     * @return List of [CommissionReport] objects created for the business members.
     */
    fun call(parameters: CommissionReportParameters): List<CommissionReport> {
        val businessToken = parameters.businessToken
        val locationNames = locationStore.resolveLocationNames(parameters.locationTokens.orEmpty())
        val isNewCommissionReportEnabled = coreFeaturesStore.isNewCommissionReportEnabled(businessToken)

        return if (isNewCommissionReportEnabled) {
            logger.info { "New Commission Report FF is ON for business [$businessToken]" }
            buildNewFlowReports(parameters, locationNames)
        } else {
            logger.info { "Creating commission report using legacy mechanism [$businessToken]" }
            createReportUsingLegacyMechanism(parameters, locationNames)
            // Legacy mechanism delegates to core-api which handles report creation externally
            emptyList()
        }
    }

    /**
     * Returns the dual report generation recipient email if dual-report generation should run,
     * or null if it should not.
     *
     * Dual report generation is skipped when:
     * - The new commission report FF is ON (dual is only for the legacy path comparison), or
     * - The `dual-report-generation` FF is not set.
     */
    fun getDualReportRecipientEmailIfEnabled(parameters: CommissionReportParameters): String? {
        if (coreFeaturesStore.isNewCommissionReportEnabled(parameters.businessToken)) return null
        return coreFeaturesStore.dualReportGenerationRecipient(parameters.businessToken)
    }

    /**
     * Enqueues a [DualCommissionReportJob] for background execution if the dual-report-generation
     * feature flag is enabled and the new commission report FF is OFF.
     *
     * No-op when dual report generation is not applicable for the given parameters.
     */
    fun enqueueDualReportIfEnabled(parameters: CommissionReportParameters) {
        val dualRecipient = getDualReportRecipientEmailIfEnabled(parameters) ?: return
        jobRequestScheduler.enqueue(
            DualCommissionReportJob(
                jobContext = requestContext.toJobContext(),
                params = DualCommissionReportJobParams(
                    businessToken = parameters.businessToken.value,
                    businessMemberToken = parameters.businessMemberToken?.value,
                    inclusiveStartDate = parameters.inclusiveStartDate.toString(),
                    exclusiveEndDate = parameters.exclusiveEndDate.toString(),
                    allowUpcoming = parameters.allowUpcoming,
                    allowOpenCheckouts = parameters.allowOpenCheckouts,
                    recipientEmailOverride = parameters.recipientEmailOverride,
                    commissionPoliciesReferenceDate = parameters.commissionPoliciesReferenceDate?.toString(),
                    dualRecipient = dualRecipient,
                    locationTokens = parameters.locationTokens?.map { it.value },
                ),
            )
        )
    }

    /**
     * Builds commission reports using the new flow, which tries to use core-payrolls commission policies and Orders
     * data directly; if either is not found for the provided parameters, it falls back to the legacy mechanism through
     * core-api.
     * Used directly when the caller needs the reports independently (e.g., dual-report generation).
     * @return List of [CommissionReport] objects, or empty list if no line items are found.
     */
    fun callNewFlow(parameters: CommissionReportParameters): List<CommissionReport> {
        val businessToken = parameters.businessToken
        val locationNames = locationStore.resolveLocationNames(parameters.locationTokens.orEmpty())
        logger.info { "Building commission reports using new flow for business [$businessToken]" }
        return buildNewFlowReports(parameters, locationNames)
    }

    @Suppress("ReturnCount", "MagicNumber", "LongMethod")
    private fun buildNewFlowReports(
        parameters: CommissionReportParameters,
        locationNames: Map<LocationToken, String>,
    ): List<CommissionReport> {
        val businessToken = parameters.businessToken

        val ordersIngestionStartDate =
            LocalDate.of(2025, 10, 1).atStartOfDay().toInstant(ZoneOffset.UTC)
        if (parameters.inclusiveStartDate.toInstant().isBefore(ordersIngestionStartDate)) {
            logger.info {
                "Report start date [${parameters.inclusiveStartDate}] is before Orders ingestion start date " +
                    "[$ordersIngestionStartDate] for Business [$businessToken]. Falling back to legacy flow."
            }
            createReportUsingLegacyMechanism(parameters, locationNames)
            return emptyList()
        }

        val businessMemberTokens = parameters.businessMemberToken?.let { listOf(it) }

        val businessMembers = businessMemberStore.search(businessToken, businessMemberTokens)

        // Fetch commission report line items for the business members within the date range
        val lineItems = commissionReportLineItemStore.search(
            businessMemberTokens = businessMembers.map { it.token },
            paidAtStartInclusive = parameters.inclusiveStartDate,
            paidAtEndExclusive = parameters.exclusiveEndDate,
            locationTokens = parameters.locationTokens,
        )

        logger.info { "Fetched ${lineItems.size} commission report line items for Business [$businessToken]" }

        if (lineItems.isEmpty()) {
            logger.info {
                "No commission report line items found for the requested criteria. Falling back to core-api"
            }
            createReportUsingLegacyMechanism(parameters, locationNames)
            return emptyList()
        }

        val businessMemberNames = businessMembers.associate { it.token to it.fullName }

        logger.info { "Fetched ${businessMembers.size} team members for Business [$businessToken]" }

        val businessTimezone = coreApiStore.retrieveBusinessTimezoneByBusinessToken(businessToken.value)

        val commissionPolicies = fetchCommissionPolicies(
            parameters = parameters,
            businessTimezone = businessTimezone,
            businessMemberTokens = listOf()
        )

        if (parameters.commissionPoliciesReferenceDate != null) {
            logger.info {
                "Using reference date for policies: " +
                    "${parameters.commissionPoliciesReferenceDate} for Business [$businessToken]"
            }
        }

        logger.info {
            "Commissions for Business [Business Token: $businessToken], commissions: " +
                "${indexCommissionPoliciesHelper.indexCommissionPolicies(commissionPolicies)}"
        }

        // Add business member full name to line items and group by business member token
        val lineItemsByBusinessMember = lineItems
            .map { it.copy(businessMemberName = businessMemberNames[it.businessMemberToken]) }
            .groupBy { it.businessMemberToken }

        val reports = lineItemsByBusinessMember.values
            .filter { it.isNotEmpty() }
            .map { memberLineItems ->
                // Scope location names to only the locations present in this member's line items,
                // since a member may only have transactions at a subset of the filtered locations.
                val memberLocationNames = memberLineItems
                    .mapNotNull { it.locationToken }
                    .distinct()
                    .mapNotNull { locationToken -> locationNames[locationToken]?.let { locationToken to it } }
                    .toMap()
                CommissionReport(memberLineItems, commissionPolicies, memberLocationNames)
            }

        logger.info { "There were ${reports.size} business members included in the commission report" }

        return reports
    }

    /**
     * Creates the commission report using the legacy mechanism (delegating to CoreApiStore).
     * This path is chosen when the 'ff-en-38569-new-commission-report' flag is OFF.
     * Note: This method delegates to core-api which handles both report creation and email sending.
     *
     * @param parameters the commission report parameters
     * @param locationNames resolved location token-to-name mapping for report headers/filenames in core-api
     */
    @Suppress("ReturnCount", "LongMethod")
    private fun createReportUsingLegacyMechanism(
        parameters: CommissionReportParameters,
        locationNames: Map<LocationToken, String>,
    ) {
        val businessToken = parameters.businessToken
        val isCustomizableCommissionEnable = coreFeaturesStore.isCustomizableCommissionsEnable(
            businessToken
        )

        if (!isCustomizableCommissionEnable) {
            logger.info {
                "Customizable Commissions disable for Business [Business Token: $businessToken], " +
                    "sending request to core-api"
            }
            coreApiStore.createCommissionReport(parameters, locationNames = locationNames)
            return
        }

        val businessTimezone = if (requestContext.legacyBusinessToken.isNullOrBlank()) {
            coreApiStore.retrieveBusinessTimezoneByBusinessToken(businessToken.value)
        } else {
            coreApiStore.retrieveBusinessTimezone(requestContext.legacyBusinessToken!!)
        }

        val releaseDate = coreFeaturesStore.customizableCommissionsReleaseDate(
            businessToken
        ).atStartOfDay(ZoneId.of(businessTimezone)).toOffsetDateTime()

        val reportEndDate = parameters.exclusiveEndDate

        val isReportEndDateAfterRelease = reportEndDate.isAfter(releaseDate)

        if (!isReportEndDateAfterRelease) {
            logger.info {
                "Report end date [$reportEndDate] is before Release date [$releaseDate] for business" +
                    " [Business Token: $businessToken], sending request to core-api"
            }
            coreApiStore.createCommissionReport(parameters, locationNames = locationNames)
            return
        }

        val commissionPolicies = fetchCommissionPolicies(
            parameters = parameters,
            businessTimezone = businessTimezone,
            businessMemberTokens = listOf()
        )

        if (parameters.commissionPoliciesReferenceDate != null) {
            logger.info {
                "Using reference date for policies in legacy mechanism: " +
                    "${parameters.commissionPoliciesReferenceDate} for Business [$businessToken]"
            }
        }

        logger.info {
            "Commissions for Business [Business Token: $businessToken], commissions: " +
                "$commissionPolicies"
        }

        val commissionPoliciesIndexed = indexCommissionPoliciesHelper.indexCommissionPolicies(
            commissionPolicies
        )

        if (commissionPolicies.isEmpty()) {
            logger.info {
                "No commissions found for Business [Business Token: $businessToken], sending " +
                    "request to core-api"
            }
            coreApiStore.createCommissionReport(parameters, commissionPoliciesIndexed, locationNames)
            return
        }

        logger.info {
            "Commissions found for Business [Business Token: $businessToken]: " +
                "$commissionPoliciesIndexed"
        }
        coreApiStore.createCommissionReport(parameters, commissionPoliciesIndexed, locationNames)
    }

    /**
     * Fetches commission policies for the given business and business member tokens.
     * Uses reference date if provided, otherwise uses current time.
     * If no policies are found, attempts to automatically migrate them from core-api.
     *
     * @param parameters The commission report parameters
     * @param businessTimezone The business timezone
     * @param businessMemberTokens The business member tokens to filter by
     * @return List of commission policies
     */
    private fun fetchCommissionPolicies(
        parameters: CommissionReportParameters,
        businessTimezone: String,
        businessMemberTokens: List<String>
    ): List<CommissionPolicy> {
        val policies = if (parameters.commissionPoliciesReferenceDate != null) {
            // Use searchActiveAtDate for historical policy lookup
            commissionPolicyStore.searchActiveAtDate(
                businessToken = parameters.businessToken.value,
                businessMemberTokens = businessMemberTokens,
                referenceDate = parameters.commissionPoliciesReferenceDate
            )
        } else {
            // Use the original search logic for current active policies
            val dateTime = OffsetDateTime.now(ZoneId.of(businessTimezone))
            commissionPolicyStore.search(
                businessToken = parameters.businessToken.value,
                businessMemberTokens = businessMemberTokens,
                effectiveDateStartsAt = dateTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.DAYS),
                effectiveDateEndsBefore = dateTime.plusDays(1).truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.DAYS),
            )
        }

        return policies
    }
}

package com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.models.commissions.report

import com.glossgenius.core.libs.tokens.domains.businesses.BusinessMemberToken
import com.glossgenius.core.libs.tokens.domains.spaces.LocationToken
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.models.commissions.CommissionPolicy
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.models.commissions.CommissionPolicyMap
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.models.commissions.CommissionPolicyRate
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.models.commissions.CommissionPolicyTargetKey
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.models.common.Amount
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.models.common.Category
import com.glossgenius.core.payrolls.models.common.totalBy

typealias LineItem = CommissionReportLineItem

/**
 * Represents a commission report for a business member.
 *
 * @property businessMemberToken The token identifying the business member for whom this report is generated.
 * @property lineItems A list of `CommissionReportLineItem` instances representing the line items in the report.
 * @property policies The [CommissionPolicyMap] used to resolve commission rates for each line item.
 * @property locationNames Resolved location token-to-name mapping for this report. Contains one entry per
 *   location included in the report. Used for email subjects, filenames, and report headers.
 */
data class CommissionReport(
    val businessMemberToken: BusinessMemberToken,
    val businessMemberName: String,
    private val lineItems: List<LineItem>,
    private val policies: CommissionPolicyMap = CommissionPolicyMap.empty(),
    val locationNames: Map<LocationToken, String> = emptyMap(),
) {
    /**
     * Lazily calculated list of `CommissionReportLineItem` with updated commission rates.
     *
     * This property maps over the `lineItems` and updates the `commissionRate` field
     * for each item using the commission policies.
     *
     * @return A list of `CommissionReportLineItem` with updated commission rates.
     */
    val rows: List<LineItem> by lazy {
        lineItems.map {
            it.copy(
                commissionRate = rateFor(it),
                applicableCommissionPolicy = getCommissionPolicyFor(it)
