Ah! Excellent question. Let me trace through the logic to see what happens when a team member only has products (no services) or only has services (no products).

Looking at the `CommissionReport.kt` file:

```kotlin
val productLineItems: List<LineItem> by lazy { rows.filter { it.category.matches(Category.PRODUCTS) } }

val serviceLineItems: List<LineItem> by lazy {
    rows.filter {
        it.category.matches(Category.SERVICES, Category.CANCELLATION_FEES)
    }
}

val summary: CommissionReportSummary by lazy {
    CommissionReportSummary(
        services = summaryItemFor(Category.SERVICES),
        products = summaryItemFor(Category.PRODUCTS),
    )
}

private fun <C : Category> summaryItemFor(category: C): CommissionReportSummaryItem<C> {
    val items = rows.filter { category.matches(it.category) }

    if (items.isEmpty()) return CommissionReportSummaryItem.zero(category, businessMemberToken)

    return CommissionReportSummaryItem.from(category, items)
}
```

So the key is in `summaryItemFor` - when there are no line items for a category (e.g., services), it returns `CommissionReportSummaryItem.zero(category, businessMemberToken)`.

This means:
- If a team member only sold products, they would have:
  - `serviceLineItems = []` (empty list)
  - `summary.services = CommissionReportSummaryItem.zero(Category.SERVICES, businessMemberToken)` - this creates a ZERO summary item
  - `productLineItems = [actual product line items]`
  - `summary.products = CommissionReportSummaryItem.from(Category.PRODUCTS, items)` - actual product summary


- If a team member only sold services, they would have:
  - `productLineItems = []` (empty list)
  - `summary.products = CommissionReportSummaryItem.zero(Category.PRODUCTS, businessMemberToken)` - this creates a ZERO summary item
  - `serviceLineItems = [actual service line items]`
  - `summary.services = CommissionReportSummaryItem.from(Category.SERVICES, items)` - actual service summary

So yes - the report includes a zero/empty row for whichever category they don't have items in. The filtering at line 172 only removes members with no line items at all, but within each report, missing categories get zero summaries instead of being omitted.

