**YES! That's exactly the issue.** 

Here's what happens:

## The Problem

Looking at `CommissionReport.kt`, when a team member has **only products** (no services):

```kotlin
val summary: CommissionReportSummary by lazy {
    CommissionReportSummary(
        services = summaryItemFor(Category.SERVICES),  // ← Returns ZERO item
        products = summaryItemFor(Category.PRODUCTS),   // ← Returns actual data
    )
}

private fun <C : Category> summaryItemFor(category: C): CommissionReportSummaryItem<C> {
    val items = rows.filter { category.matches(it.category) }

    if (items.isEmpty()) return CommissionReportSummaryItem.zero(category, businessMemberToken)
    //                          ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
    //                          THIS creates a zero/empty summary item!

    return CommissionReportSummaryItem.from(category, items)
}
```

The `CommissionReportSummaryItem.zero()` method creates a summary item with:
- `businessMemberToken` = the team member
- All amounts = `$0.00`
- All counts = `0`
- Empty lists for services/products/clients

So the report will show:

```
Services Section:
  Team Member Name | 0 services | $0.00 sales | $0.00 commission  ← EMPTY ROW

Products Section:
  Team Member Name | 5 products | $500.00 sales | $50.00 commission  ← ACTUAL DATA
```

